<item>
            <title>[SPR-1210] Declarative custom editor setup doesn&apos;t work</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-1210</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m trying to register a custom editor in a declarative way:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;bean id=&quot;customEditorConfigurer&quot; class=&quot;org.springframework.beans.factory.config.CustomEditorConfigurer&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;property name=&quot;customEditors&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;map&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;entry key=&quot;mypackage.myType&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                &amp;lt;bean class=&quot;mypacke.myEditor&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;/entry&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;/map&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;/property&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/bean&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The Editor gets initialized but isn&apos;t used for wrapping my type. If I register the same editor in the initBinder() method of my controller, everything works fine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I already tried to find a solution by asking in the forum (&lt;a href=&quot;http://forum.springframework.org/viewtopic.php?t=7797&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://forum.springframework.org/viewtopic.php?t=7797&lt;/a&gt;) but had no luck.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is it a bug?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
